==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stippling
<hw>Stip"pling</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
}</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Engraving)</fld> <def>A mode of execution
which produces the effect by dots or small points instead of
lines.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Paint.)</fld> <def>A mode of execution in which a
flat or even tint is produced by many small touches.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stiptic</ent>⟦br⟧
